      <long>
	<en>Secure password sharing integration for GLPI.
Sharing passwords is an IT nightmare, no matter which ITSM tool you use. Zero-trust is the way to go, although it is only sometimes possible and only for some scenarios.
One-Time Secret is an excellent tool to overcome this common issue. By sharing a burnable one-time open link with your interlocutor, you will forever forget passwords stored in emails or messaging tools, available for indiscrete eyes.
Secret Link expiration and additional Passphrase are the icings on the cake.

But opening a website, copying and pasting, sending a messageâ€¦, well, the whole process may be improved.

This is where our One-Time Secret GLPI integration excels.

A streamlined experience for both techs and end-users.
         </en>
       </long>
